{"id":71705,"title":"The role of the American College of Surgeons' cancer program accreditation in influencing oncologic outcomes.","abstract":"The multidisciplinary Commission on Cancer (CoC) and National Accreditation Program for Breast Centers (NAPBC), administered by the American College of Surgeons (ACoS), defines evidence and consensus-based standards, require an operational infrastructure, collect high quality cancer data, and validate compliance with standards through external peer review. A survey of our constituents confirms a high level of agreement that accreditation is regarded as important in improving oncologic outcomes through compliance with standards that include continuous quality improvement.","date":"2014-09-25","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25042831","annotations":[{"name":"Peer review","weight":0.520145,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peer_review"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.454937,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"},{"name":"Accreditation","weight":0.399023,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accreditation"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.394143,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Quality management","weight":0.306474,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quality_management"},{"name":"Verification and validation","weight":0.197283,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verification_and_validation"},{"name":"American College of Surgeons","weight":0.141968,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_College_of_Surgeons"},{"name":"Data","weight":0.111485,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data"},{"name":"Infrastructure","weight":0.0629772,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infrastructure"},{"name":"Oncology","weight":0.0546925,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oncology"},{"name":"Technical standard","weight":0.0488